714330f.text:
71st Street, south side, east from and including Park
uvenue. The buildings in the foreground are a part of the
Presbyterian Hospital. The hosptal has already moved uptown

months.

722334f.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 71st Street
722334f.text:
752 and 754 Park Avenue, west side, between 71st and 72nd Streets,
showing part of the corner house, 78 West 72nd Street. At right,
No. 752 will be demolished in 1929. It is the northorn half of
a double house (sec picture of N.W. corner of 71st Street).
About 1912.

722333f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 71st Street
722333f-a.text:
748 Park Avenue at N.W. corner of 71st Street, built about 1906.
This building, together with the double house 750-52 and the
Presbyterian Nurses' Home, seen to the left on 71st Street,
will be replaced in 1929 by a 17-story apartment building.
About 1912.
The Pictorial News Co., Photographer.
0ift of E. M. Jenks.
